# Kyro Workflow (Cursor)

Use Kyro for sprint-based development on this project. Kyro is agent-agnostic — any model in Cursor can follow these instructions.

## Required Reading

Before forge, status, or wrap-up work, read:
- `.agents/orchestrator.md`
- `.skills/sprint-forge/SKILL.md`
- `.skills/qa-review/SKILL.md`

## Artifact Root

Persist all sprint output under `.agents/sprint-forge/{scope}/` (README, ROADMAP, findings, sprints, RE-ENTRY-PROMPTS, state.json).

## Workflow Intents

Cursor does not register Kyro slash commands by default. Use manual intents:

| Intent | Action |
|--------|--------|
| `forge` | Analyze → plan → implement → review → close |
| `status` | Read artifacts; report progress and debt |
| `wrap-up` | Update retro, re-entry prompts, and learned rules |

## Harness Config

In `config.json`, set:
```json
"harness": {
  "id": "cursor",
  "capabilities": {
    "slash_commands": false,
    "subagents": true,
    "post_edit_hooks": false,
    "project_memory": false
  },
  "enforcement": "manual"
}
```

Adjust `subagents` based on whether your Cursor setup supports parallel subagents.

## Deterministic Checks

When `harness.enforcement` is `manual`, run after edits:
```bash
npm run check:post-edit
npm run check:pre-commit
```

Never skip gates in `config.json` → `gates.always_gate` without explicit user approval.
